<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1897" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1897">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of Spain</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: With reference to your
                            excellency’s note of November 16 last, I have the honor to inform you
                            that His Majesty’s Government, according to a telegram I have received,
                            concurs in extending from the 21st of June, 1915, to the 15th of
                            February, 1916, the time set by the Treaty of September 15, 1914, for
                            the appointment of the International Commission therein specified.</p>
                        <p>In so informing your excellency, I avail myself of this opportunity to
                            renew to you the assurance of my highest consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>